Name: Happy Victoria
Description: On the 7th of April, 2011, in Sofia, a new Happy restaurant welcomed its first guests – “Happy Victoria”. Thanks to the cozy atmosphere, which the restaurant offers, you will feel really special. The numerous aquariums inhabited by exotic fish will contribute to the unique experience.

Name: Happy Kableshkov
Description: Happy Kableshkov is located in the Sofia district Manastirski Livadi on the ground floor of shopping center Friends on nearly 700 square meters. The interior is completely different from the other restaurants in the chain. The designers’ new concept is based on red accents, paneling on the walls in a dark chocolate color and a seats made of luxurious leather. The restaurant is equipped with powerful sound system. Lighting that is imported from the U.S., is unique, with extremely irregular shape and unusual opportunities for directing light rays.

Name: Taj Mahal
Description: India sounds like an invitation to an adventure with a flavour of spices. Besides the mysticism and romance, India touches the hearts of everybody that had the chance to taste its exquisite cuisine. The preparation of the Inian food is a skillful ritual and a challenge to all senses. The Indians say that the art of cooking is a gift from the gods.

Name: Capo Mediterranean Restaurant
Description: We are pleased to welcome you to the restaurant "Capo"! With great love and diligence of our entire team hope during your stay here to deliver delight your senses by selecting always fresh and appropriate for the season products carer close and our shef- Svetlin Ivanov. It presents Mediterranean cuisine in our menu in the form of specially selected and prepared dishes. To tap to the Mediterranean, it relies on fresh products such as fish and seafood delicacies. They remain leaders in our menu for our weekly fresh supplies from ports in Thessaloniki. Our goal is to transform the appearance of former Greek restaurant Kumbare, by enriching the menu with dishes such as as fresh pasta, selected Italian cheeses and sausages, homemade Kaiser young salmon and beef from Argentina, done on a plate or in your choice.  Aesthetically, our inspiration stems from the sophistication of the Italian design, which speaks interior atmosphere of the restaurant. We have set of furniture and accessories supplied directly by Italy, in order to create an atmosphere as close as possible to the coastssouthern Italy.

Larger tables are separated from the others in separate tents, which creates more privacy. Candles further soft  atmosphere. The restaurant has got a VIP lounge, which can be separated from the main hall. The fireplace and style of the VIP lounge are ideal for family gatherings or private dining. Additionally, there are two smaller halls with 20-30 seats that are suitable for private parties.

Description: Restaurant Kotiloto is a unique place characterized with authentic taste of Serbian cuisine and perfect service. Situated in Sofia, the restaurant offers delicious specialties made by original recipes from the home of Serbian grill – Leskovac. The traditional dishes are personally prepared by Chef Dalibor Marinkovich – Daci who won golden medal in Skariada 2009 festival. Every dish is made with care and leaves unforgettable memory of homemade food.

Name: Lazy Life & Food
Description: Located at the base of the Vitosha mountain Lazy offers you a laid back concept of life so that you enjoy your lunch or dinner smiling and stress free. At Lazy dishes are not just a delight to the eye and a treat to your senses but also a good reason to smile and enjoy those special moments of life.

Our wine selection is specifically designed for every dish. In the last days of the working week, we enjoy elegant and chic nights with party music selected by our DJ, champagne and cocktails.

Name: India House
Description: The cuisine of India is one of the world's most diverse cuisines, characterized by its sophisticated and subtle use of the many spices, vegetables, grains and fruits grown across India. The cuisine of each geographical region includes a wide assortment of dishes and cooking techniques reflecting the varied demographics of the ethnically diverse Indian subcontinent. India's religious beliefs and culture have played an influential role in the evolution of its cuisine

Name: Floret Restaurant & Bar

Open from early morning until the late hours of the evening, this is the place for energizing breakfast, quick business lunch, unforgettable dinners and stylish parties. Name: Mamma Mia Slatina
Description: Pizza, which has become one of the most favourite foods of people around the world, originates in Italy, more precisely from the coastal city of Naples. Approximately 500 years ago Naples started expanding as the greatest part of its population consisted of workers from different industries. These same workers were relatively low-paid and they were not able to afford the lifestyle of the middle class, nor of the high society of the country. This is the reason why they tried to save money from everything possible, including food.

Id: It is exactly the struggle of the people to reduce their food expenses to the greatest extent that leads to the creation of the archetype of modern pizza. It is called „pizzaioli“ and represents flatbread with tomato sauce. You can sometimes find it topped with cheese, anchovies, garlic and various spices. This early type of pizza is not only pretty cheap but also satisfies the needs of the Neapolitan workers. Due to this fact we can freely say that in its essence pizza is considered a low-key food for the poor population.

Description: https://www.facebook.com/MammaMia.bg/
